{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28ae85466ffekqL19wETvDpf09","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d7517c1610011tzsHGjxZwletm","parts":[{"id":"prt_d7517c8be001F61s96RQS9rJuG","messageID":"msg_d7517c1610011tzsHGjxZwletm","sessionID":"ses_28ae85466ffekqL19wETvDpf09","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9d3f1ba5bd9c4984872cf837","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.rst</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: .. image:: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/control/badges/version.svg\n2:    :target: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/control\n3: \n4: .. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/control.svg\n5:    :target: https://pypi.org/project/control/\n6: \n7: .. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/python-package-conda.yml/badge.svg\n8:    :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/python-package-conda.yml\n9: \n10: .. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/install_examples.yml/badge.svg\n11:    :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/install_examples.yml\n12: \n13: .. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/control-slycot-src.yml/badge.svg\n14:    :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/control-slycot-src.yml\n15: \n16: .. image:: https://coveralls.io/repos/python-control/python-control/badge.svg\n17:    :target: https://coveralls.io/r/python-control/python-control\n18: \n19: Python Control Systems Library\n20: ==============================\n21: \n22: The Python Control Systems Library is a Python module that implements basic\n23: operations for analysis and design of feedback control systems.\n24: \n25: Have a go now!\n26: --------------\n27: Try out the examples in the examples folder using the binder service.\n28: \n29: .. image:: https://mybinder.org/badge_logo.svg\n30:  :target: https://mybinder.org/v2/gh/python-control/python-control/HEAD\n31: \n32: The package can also be installed on Google Colab using the commands::\n33: \n34:   %pip install control\n35:   import control as ct\n36: \n37: Features\n38: --------\n39: \n40: - Linear input/output systems in state-space and frequency domain\n41: - Block diagram algebra: serial, parallel, feedback, and other interconnections\n42: - Time response: initial, step, impulse\n43: - Frequency response: Bode, Nyquist, and Nichols plots\n44: - Control analysis: stability, reachability, observability, stability margins, root locus\n45: - Control design: eigenvalue placement, linear quadratic regulator, sisotool, hinfsyn, rootlocus_pid_designer\n46: - Estimator design: linear quadratic estimator (Kalman filter)\n47: - Nonlinear systems: optimization-based control, describing functions, differential flatness\n48: \n49: Links\n50: -----\n51: \n52: - Project home page: https://python-control.org\n53: - Source code repository: https://github.com/python-control/python-control\n54: - Documentation: https://python-control.readthedocs.io/\n55: - Issue tracker: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/issues\n56: - Mailing list: https://sourceforge.net/p/python-control/mailman/\n57: \n58: Dependencies\n59: ------------\n60: \n61: The package requires numpy, scipy, and matplotlib.  In addition, some routines\n62: use a module called slycot, that is a Python wrapper around some FORTRAN\n63: routines.  Many parts of python-control will work without slycot, but some\n64: functionality is limited or absent, and installation of slycot is recommended\n65: (see below). The Slycot wrapper can be found at:\n66: \n67: https://github.com/python-control/Slycot\n68: \n69: \n70: Installation\n71: ============\n72: \n73: Conda and conda-forge\n74: ---------------------\n75: \n76: The easiest way to get started with the Control Systems library is\n77: using `Conda <https://conda.io>`_.\n78: \n79: The Control Systems library has packages available using the `conda-forge\n80: <https://conda-forge.org>`_ Conda channel, and as of Slycot version\n81: 0.3.4, binaries for that package are available for 64-bit Windows,\n82: OSX, and Linux.\n83: \n84: To install both the Control Systems library and Slycot in an existing\n85: conda environment, run::\n86: \n87:   conda install -c conda-forge control slycot\n88: \n89: Mixing packages from conda-forge and the default conda channel can\n90: sometimes cause problems with dependencies, so it is usually best to\n91: instally NumPy, SciPy, and Matplotlib from conda-forge as well.\n92: \n93: Pip\n94: ---\n95: \n96: To install using pip::\n97: \n98:   pip install slycot   # optional; see below\n99:   pip install control\n100: \n101: If you install Slycot using pip you'll need a development environment\n102: (e.g., Python development files, C and Fortran compilers).  Pip\n103: installation can be particularly complicated for Windows.\n104: \n105: Installing from source\n106: ----------------------\n107: \n108: To install from source, get the source code of the desired branch or release\n109: from the github repository or archive, unpack, and run from within the\n110: toplevel `python-control` directory::\n111: \n112:   pip install .\n113: \n114: Article and Citation Information\n115: ================================\n116: \n117: An `article <https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/9683368>`_ about\n118: the library is available on IEEE Explore. If the Python Control Systems Library helped you in your research, please cite::\n119: \n120:   @inproceedings{python-control2021,\n121:     title={The Python Control Systems Library (python-control)},\n122:     author={Fuller, Sawyer and Greiner, Ben and Moore, Jason and\n123:             Murray, Richard and van Paassen, Ren{\\'e} and Yorke, Rory},\n124:     booktitle={60th IEEE Conference on Decision and Control (CDC)},\n125:     pages={4875--4881},\n126:     year={2021},\n127:     organization={IEEE}\n128:   }\n129: \n130: or the GitHub site: https://github.com/python-control/python-control\n131: \n132: Development\n133: ===========\n134: \n135: Code\n136: ----\n137: \n138: You can check out the latest version of the source code with the command::\n139: \n140:   git clone https://github.com/python-control/python-control.git\n141: \n142: Testing\n143: -------\n144: \n145: You can run the unit tests with `pytest`_ to make sure that everything is\n146: working correctly.  Inside the source directory, run::\n147: \n148:   pytest -v\n149: \n150: or to test the installed package::\n151: \n152:   pytest --pyargs control -v\n153: \n154: .. _pytest: https://docs.pytest.org/\n155: \n156: License\n157: -------\n158: \n159: This is free software released under the terms of `the BSD 3-Clause\n160: License <https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause>`_.  There is no\n161: warranty; not even for merchantability or fitness for a particular\n162: purpose.  Consult LICENSE for copying conditions.\n163: \n164: When code is modified or re-distributed, the LICENSE file should\n165: accompany the code or any subset of it, however small.  As an\n166: alternative, the LICENSE text can be copied within files, if so\n167: desired.\n168: \n169: Contributing\n170: ------------\n171: \n172: Your contributions are welcome!  Simply fork the GitHub repository and send a\n173: `pull request`_.\n174: \n175: .. _pull request: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/pulls\n176: \n177: Please see the `Developer's Wiki`_ for detailed instructions.\n178: \n179: .. _Developer's Wiki: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/wiki\n\n(End of file - total 179 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".. image:: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/control/badges/version.svg\n   :target: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/control\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/control.svg\n   :target: https://pypi.org/project/control/\n\n.. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/python-package-conda.yml/badge.svg\n   :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/python-package-conda.yml\n\n.. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/install_examples.yml/badge.svg\n   :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/install_examples.yml\n\n.. image:: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/control-slycot-src.yml/badge.svg\n   :target: https://github.com/python-control/python-control/actions/workflows/control-slycot-src.yml\n\n.. image:: https://coveralls.io/repos/python-control/python-control/badge.svg\n   :target: https://coveralls.io/r/python-control/python-control\n\nPython Control Systems Library\n==============================","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.rst","time":{"start":1775785986523,"end":1775785986539}}}]}
